content.description: To the right of Shoot 'Em Up.

Clip two easy bolts and then climb pinches, sidepulls, and pockets to a series of chalked holds below the 5th bolt.  Throw up and right to a horn right below the 5th bolt and then continue on decent stuff to the 6th bolt.  The draw hangs down below onto this horn which is a bit annoying.  There is also a crimp you can hit left of the horn.  If you move right after the next bolt and clip the chains of Downloader it is 5.11c.  You probably want a long draw on the 6th bolt if you move right.  And it is a reachy move to clip the chains...be careful once you pull up rope to clip.  Much easier once you place two draws on the chains to clip.

For the full climb move left after the 6th bolt into a more delicate, crimpy face and finish another 30-40 feet higher.
content.protection: 6 bolts for the 5.11c and maybe +/10 bolts for the 12a.
content.location: Third bolt line left of the right side of the wall.

content.description: A short, bouldery route with powerful compression moves, and a challenging lip sequence.
content.protection:
This route requires quickdraws.  Lower off anchors.

A 50 meter rope is required.
content.location: Just left of In the Meantime(12b) at the right end of the Ammo Dump Wall.  This is the first route that goes out the roof.

content.description:
Shoot Em' Up is a very challenging route with great rock, and thought provoking sequences.  Large, pumpy moves lead to a tough boulder problem, a hard clip, and the crux- a difficult lip encounter.

Personally, this route felt hard for 13a.   Regardless of the grade, this route epitomizes maple- fun.
content.protection: Fully bolted, including the anchors.  A 50 meter rope will easily get you back to the ground.
content.location: Just right of Bomb Squad on the left side of the Ammo Dump Wall.

content.description: Easy climbing down low to a decent shake out, then power through a boulder problem to the lip and mantel.
content.protection: Bolts.  Usually has a few fixed draws up high.  The second to last draw would be hard to hang if it is not already fixed.
content.location: Toward the left end of ammo dump.  Right of football, left of Bomb squad.

content.description: Start on Low angle slab clip two bolts then move through crux to big jug.  Shake out and pull the easy little roof. Chains with new biners up behind a tree.
content.protection: Bolts to chains w/ new biners
content.location: On the very end of the ammo dump wall, just before the chimney.

content.description:
To the left of

Watermelon Sugar

.  Super fun route with a hard clip at the lip.
This is a bouldery route that has the potential for a scary clip. It is named after the "football" like cobble at the top of the route.
content.location: This route is just left of Point Blank

content.description: Good climbing on vertical face.  Traverse a few moves up top and clip chains. Another good warm up or warm down for the area.
content.location: 2nd line of bolts on ammo dump- left of devils play thing

content.description: Climb relatively positive, but pumpy holds to a decent rest about 12 feet below the anchors.  Finish on sidepulls up and left.  Try not to annoy or be annoyed by the pigeons.
content.protection: about +/-10 bolts to the chains, easy to count from below.
content.location: First climb on the right of Ammo Dump wall...just left of the 5.13a climb called Loser on the Cobble wall.

content.description: A bouldery route ends on the same anchors as Point Blank.
content.location: This route is in between Point Blank and Shoot'em Up.
